#. translators: %s: link to Form Handler Inspector
#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:819
#, php-format
msgid "Unmapped fields are silently ignored by Pardot. Use the %s on the Settings tab to verify which of these fields are configured in each of your form handlers."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:820
#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:899
msgid "Form Handler Inspector"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:825
msgid "Error handling"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:826
msgid "The plugin handles form errors in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:829
msgid "Client-side validation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:829
msgid "Before the form is submitted to Pardot, JavaScript checks all required fields and field formats using the HTML5 Constraint Validation API. If any fields are invalid, an error message is shown above the fields and submission is blocked until the issues are corrected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:832
msgid "Pardot server-side errors"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:832
msgid "If Pardot rejects a submission (for example, an email address fails its validation rules), it redirects back to the form page with an errorMessage parameter and the submitted field values in the URL. The plugin automatically detects this redirect, displays the error message in a notice above the form fields, and re-populates the visible fields so the visitor does not need to re-type their data."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:835
msgid "The error notice is styled with a red left border and appears inside the form, spanning the full width above all fields. It is only shown when errors are present and is cleared automatically when the visitor resubmits successfully."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:841
msgid "When you are logged in as an administrator, a small \"Attribution (N)\" menu appears in the WordPress admin bar on every page of the site. It shows the current value of each attribution cookie — or \"(not set)\" if that cookie has not been captured yet."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bol-admin-page.php:844
msgid "The menu also includes a \"Clear all cookies\" link. Clicking it deletes all eight attribution cookies and reloads the page, so you can simulate a fresh visitor without opening a private browser window."
